      "lesson title": "AI on Edge Devices: Security Trade-Offs",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Running artificial intelligence directly on edge devices, such as smartphones, smart speakers, and IoT sensors, offers real advantages in speed and privacy, but it also introduces a distinct set of security challenges that are worth understanding. Unlike centralised systems where data is processed on a remote server, edge devices handle sensitive information locally, which means the device itself becomes a potential target for attack. In this lesson, we will explore the key trade-offs between running models on-device versus relying on cloud-based infrastructure, looking at factors such as data exposure, physical security risks, and the limitations of keeping software up to date. By the end, you will have a clearer picture of when edge deployment makes sense and what precautions are worth putting in place. No prior security expertise is needed, just a curiosity about how AI systems work in the real world.",
